{
  "abstract": "The ICRISAT Village Level Studies (VLS) offer a unique\r\nopportunity to look at changes in villages over time. This activity\r\noffers a valuable and unique opportunity to examine the gender\r\nimplications of changes in production systems. The existing\r\npanel data for 6 villages in the Semi-Arid Tropics (SAT) of India\r\nfrom 1975-84 and 2001 onwards captures and documents the\r\nchanges in the farming systems and rural households",
